description: A recent social media post by BJP leader Tathagata Roy has sparked controversy, suggesting that circumcision should be a determining factor for the religious identity of male applicants seeking citizenship under the CAA. The TMC has criticized the comment as a "vulgar jibe," questioning the BJP's underlying agenda. The CAA aims to provide Indian citizenship to persecuted minorities from Afghanistan, Bangladesh, and Pakistan who arrived in India by 2014.
title: BJP neta touts ‘circumcision test’ for citizenship seekers, stirs row

description: Rahul Gandhi launches INDIA bloc's campaign at Shivaji Park, addressing corruption, threats to democracy, and BJP tactics. Mentions Ashok Chavan, NDA's white paper, opposition leaders, historical locations, and political confrontations.
title: Ex-Cong leader wept, said forced to join BJP: Rahul

description: Facing unrest in Matua-dominated areas of Bengal over the CAA's schedule 1A requirement for Bangladeshi documents, Union Minister Shantanu Thakur, also Bongaon MP, plans to seek citizenship under the CAA to counter alleged misinformation by the TMC. Thakur's announcement on Saturday follows recent protests in Nadia's Chakdah and threats of further demonstrations by the Sara Bharat Matua Mahasangha in Malda.
title: Will apply under CAA to debunk TMC claims: Union minister from WB

description: Housing experts, industry leaders, and builders gathered at The Times of India's property summit in Gurugram to discuss real estate trends. The event, with a focus on innovation and urban planning, attracted key figures like Gaurav Jain of NAREDCO, who praised Rera in his address. The summit, in association with REA India, highlighted the evolving realty market.
title: ‘Realty sector has undergone seismic shift in last 10-12 years’

description: Golaghat district police have apprehended a deputy superintendent of police (DSP) for allegedly sexually assaulting a minor employed as a domestic worker at the officer's residence. The DSP, stationed at the Lachit Borphukan Police Academy in Golaghat, Assam, has had an FIR filed against him at Dergaon police station. Charges under Section 376 and 506 of the IPC  have been levied against him following a complaint from the 15-year-old girl's family, as per police reports.
title: DSP held for sexual assault of minor house help in Assam

description: Tamil Nadu Governor R N Ravi has turned down CM M K Stalin's proposal to reinstate K Ponmudy as a minister. The Governor cited Ponmudy's tainted corruption record as the reason for rejecting the recommendation. Ponmudy, who previously served as the higher education minister, had to step down following a corruption conviction by the Madras High Court last December.
title: ‘Tainted’: TN governor nixes Stalin bid to reinduct ex-minister Ponmudy

description: The Chinese military restated its claim over Arunachal Pradesh, asserting it as part of China's territory. This comes after India dismissed objections to PM Modi's visit to the state. Zhang made the remarks in response to India’s enhancement of its military readiness through Sela Tunnel in Arunachal Pradesh, according to a report posted on Chinese defence ministry’s website Friday.
title: Arunachal inherent part of China, claims Chinese military

description: Delhi CM Kejriwal faces ED summonses linked to alleged scams, stirring AAP-BJP dispute over legality and motives. Atishi accuses BJP of hindering Kejriwal's election campaign. BJP denies claims, criticizing AAP's behavior and defending ED's actions.
title: Day after bail, Arvind Kejriwal gets 2 ED summons

description: RSS general secretary Dattatreya Hosabale stated, "A movement like Ramjanmabhoomi is not necessary for Kashi and Mathura shrines."  “The matter (Kashi and Mathura) is being heard in court. Even the solution to the Ayodhya dispute finally came through courts. Where’s the need for a movement of a similar scale if the matter can be resolved by the judiciary?” he asked.
title: No need for Ram temple-like movement to reclaim other shrines, says Hosabale

description: Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh's Akhil Bharatiya Pratinidhi Sabha (ABPS) has extended Dattatreya Hosabale's tenure as national general secretary for another three years. The meeting also urged citizens to vote in large numbers. RSS also underscored its concern as it highlighted farmers’ agitation as an attempt to spread anarchy in Punjab, condemned atrocities in Sandeshkhali, and expressed worry over the ethnic conflict in Manipur.
title: Anti-Bharat forces plotting new designs to disrupt: RSS

description: A tragic incident occurred in UP’s Moradabad district as a four-year-old boy named Mohd Ahad drowned in a deep water-filled pit at a brick kiln on Saturday night. Mohd Javed, the boy's father and a laborer at the kiln, was occupied with loading bricks onto a tractor when his son wandered towards the pit to play. Despite his efforts to locate Ahad, he was unable to find him.
title: 4-year-old boy drowns in pit at brick kiln in UP’s Moradabad district

description: Indian military personnel in the Maldives are being replaced by civilians for aviation platforms. Discussions between the countries cover deputation progress, upcoming personnel replacement deadlines, economic cooperation, developmental projects, bilateral cooperation, and humanitarian services.
title: India & Maldives review troop pullout, discuss economic ties

description: The Gujarat high court has served notices to the state government, Centre, and Google India Pvt Ltd following the blocking of an engineer's account for alleged "explicit child abuse." The engineer, Neel Shukla, had shared a childhood photo of his grandmother bathing him at age two, which led to the suspension of his account by Google's AI system in April last year.
title: Google labels childhood pic ‘porn’, draws HC notice

description: In Mukerian, Punjab, a wanted criminal involved in eight cases fired at a police team during a raid on Sunday, resulting in the death of a constable. The incident occurred in Mansurpur village when the police went to arrest Rana Mansoorpur based on a tip-off. Mansoorpur shot at the officers and managed to flee. Unfortunately, one of the bullets struck constable Amritpal Singh in the chest.
title: Criminal opens fire at Punjab cops during raid at home, kills 1

description: Trinamool Congress and JD(U) received electoral bond donations without disclosing donors' identities. While JD(U) revealed some donors, TMC did not, citing reliance on SBI's KYC process to identify donors through unique bond numbers.
title: Poll bonds were just left at our offices, don’t know by whom: TMC & JD(U)

description: Hydroxyurea, a drug used to treat sickle cell anaemia, will now be accessible in India for Rs 600 per vial, a fraction of the cost of imported versions. Unlike the global brands priced at around Rs 77,000 per vial, needing specific storage at 2-8 degrees Celsius, the Indian variant by Delhi-based Akums Drugs and Pharmaceuticals Ltd. remains stable at room temperature.
title: Desi sickle cell anaemia drug to cost less than 1% of imported versions

description: The Chhattisgarh Economic Offences Wing (EOW) has included former CM Bhupesh Baghel in an FIR related to the alleged Rs 6,000-crore Mahadev Book online betting scam. The FIR, filed on March 4 based on an ED complaint, came to light after Lok Sabha elections were announced. EOW remained tight-lipped but a copy of the FIR shows that the case has been registered under IPC.
title: Baghel named in Mahadev app FIR; political vendetta: Ex-CM

description: The family of late singer-rapper Shubhdeep Singh, known as Sidhu Moose Wala, announced the birth of a baby boy through IVF by his 58-year-old mother Charan Kaur. The newborn was pictured next to a framed portrait of a young Sikh with the caption "Legends never die". This joyous event comes almost 22 months after the tragic death of Shubhdeep Singh in Punjab's Mansa.
title: 22 months after Moose Wala’s death, his mom gives birth to boy at 58

description: he Economic Offences Unit (EOU) of Bihar Police has apprehended 313 individuals in relation to the alleged question paper leak during the Bihar Public Service Commission's (BPSC) teacher recruitment examination (TRE) 3.0 held on March 15. Following their arrest, a Patna civil court has placed all the suspects in judicial custody, with 266 of them, including 88 women, being housed at Beur Central Jail.
title: 313 arrested for Bihar teacher recruitment exam paper leak

description: Election Commission data on electoral bonds revealed major parties hiding donors' details. SC awaits SBI's unique bond numbers. Some parties disclosed partial info. Donations from unrelated states noted, fueling curiosity for further disclosures.
title: No details on 94% of poll bond donations as Big 5 stonewall

description: On a bright morning in January, students from 50 schools in Mumbai gathered at St Willibrord High School in Nalasopara. The classrooms had turned into AI hubs, with screens replacing textbooks. Students engaged with questions like 'How do self-driving cars use AI?' and 'What is the impact of AI on jobs?'
title: Can’t beat it? Embrace it: Schools in Mumbai transform AI into ally

description: The age-old preference for adopting a male child among childless couples in India is witnessing a significant shift under the Hindu Adoption and Maintenance Act (HAMA). Recent data from the past two years reveals a notable increase in the adoption of girl children. The statistics disclosed by the Union government clearly indicate a departure from the longstanding tradition rooted in Vedic times.
title: Male bias gone, Hindu couples prefer to adopt girls: Govt data

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin clinched a historic fifth term, securing a landslide victory in the presidential polls with no serious challengers. Early results show Putin capturing 88% of the votes, solidifying his position as Russia's longest-serving leader, surpassing Josef Stalin. Putin, a former KGB agent who ascended to power in 1999, now cements his place in Russian political history.
title: Putin 'wins' Russian presidential polls for record fifth-term

description: Voice cloning scams like the one targeting Sarita Khanna's daughter are on the rise, with criminals using sophisticated methods to deceive victims for ransom. Despite legal provisions, tracking these scammers remains challenging.
title: Fooled by your own kid? Chilling rise of AI voice cloning scams

description: PM Modi instructed ministers to prioritize govt work during elections, focusing on major initiatives and efficient implementation. Plans for the first 100 days and 5 years of the new govt are crucial, along with addressing Election Commission roadmap and achieving 'Viksit Bharat' vision.
title: PM to mantris: Draw up plan for 1st 100 days of next govt

description: AIADMK received Rs 6 crore in electoral bonds from major donors like India Cements and Chennai Super Kings. Meanwhile, NCP, led by Sharad Pawar, received Rs 65.6 crore from various sources, including Neotia Foundation and Bharti Airtel. Shiv Sena only received 227 crore, with details submitted by it showing bonds were issued to it from Mumbai.
title: CSK, India Cements top bond donors of AIADMK

description: Recent Election Commission data reveals Congress leading in electoral bond receipts over Trinamool Congress (TMC). Despite Trinamool's initial advantage, Congress received more bonds. The data of 2017-18 and 2018-19 combined put the Trinamool ahead of Congress. A crucial period before the 2019 Lok Sabha polls showed significant differences in funding amounts.
title: Cong 2nd-largest gainer from electoral bonds, slightly ahead of TMC, shows fresh data

description: Cash-strapped Pakistan is set to formally request a bailout package from the International Monetary Fund (IMF) through the Extended Fund Facility (EFF). Reports suggest Islamabad may seek over 8 billion US dollars during the upcoming IMF/World Bank spring meetings in Washington, DC, from April 15 to 20. It is expected that Pakistan may request for enhanced quota like it did in 2008.
title: Pakistan to seek larger IMF bailout package of over $8 billion

description: A spirited women's team washed away Royal Challengers Bangalore's 16 years of hurt and disappointment, landing their maiden title which came through an eight-wicket win over Delhi Capitals in front of a cheering full house in the Women's Premier League final in New Delhi on Sunday.
title: Spinners, Perry hand RCB maiden WPL title

description: Future Gaming, led by Santiago Martin, donated significantly to DMK through electoral bonds. Other major donors like Mega Infrastructure, Sun TV Network, and JD(S) also contributed, raising transparency concerns in political funding practices.
title: DMK got ₹509 crore in electoral bonds from ‘lottery king’

description: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu criticised calls for elections in Israel from the United States, asserting that these calls were unwarranted amidst the ongoing conflict with Hamas. According to an AP report, US Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, a prominent Jewish figure and staunch supporter of Israel, had urged for fresh elections, saying Netanyahu “lost his way”.
title: Netanyahu slams US lawmaker's call for election

description: Days after PM Modi's relentless critique of regional parties for fostering "dynastic politics" at his public addresses in Bihar earlier this month, speculation suggests that RJD president Lalu Prasad is contemplating the political debut of his another daughter, Rohini Acharya. Currently, Lalu has three offspring actively engaged in politics—his elder daughter Misa Bharti, along with both his sons, Tej Pratap Yadav and Tejashwi Yadav, who have served as former ministers.
title: Rohini Acharya to contest from father Lalu's home seat?
Adani to invest $14 billion in FY25

description: Reflecting on her performance, RCB spin bowling all-rounder ShreyankaPatil expressed that even a slight turn on the pitch unleashes her full potential, likening herself to a "different beast" with the ball in hand. Patil, who claimed the Purple Cap for most wickets by a player in the tournament after her exploits, has 13 wickets in eight games at an average of 12.07, with the best bowling figures of 4/12.
title: 'I am a different beast when I...': RCB's Shreyanka Patil

description: The third meeting of the India-Maldives High Level Core Group focused on ongoing deployment of Indian technical personnel and bilateral cooperation. Discussions included providing humanitarian aid through Indian aviation, strengthening trade and investment, and enhancing people-to-people linkages. Both nations agreed on viable solutions to ensure the continued operation of Indian aviation platforms in the Maldives.
title: India, Maldives hold high-level core group meeting
Akhilesh skips Rahul's yatra, sends letter praising its success

description: Rahul Gandhi ended his Bharat Jodo Nyay Yatra with a mega rally at Mumbai's Shivaji Park. The event saw several opposition leaders in attendance, including RJD's Tejashwi Yadav, Tamil Nadu chief minister MK Stalin, Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge, Sharad Pawar, Farooq Abdullah, Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, Uddhav Thackeray, and Mehbooba Mufti.
title: 'Soul of King in EVM': Rahul flays BJP as INDIA bloc bolsters unity efforts ahead of LS polls
Bulgaria thanks India for rescuing nationals from hijacked ship: What Jaishankar said

description: In sports, it's often evident that the home team benefits from the support of the crowd. However, this wasn't the scenario during the Women's Premier League final between Delhi Capitals Women and Royal Challengers Bangalore in Delhi on Sunday.
title: 'I know this is Delhi...': Shastri left amazed as Mandhana gets huge cheer
‘Noon against Putin’: Thousands of Russians protest against polls
PM Modi urges people to get down from light tower at rally

description: A man was arrested in Russia's Moldova on Sunday for throwing two Molotov cocktails at the embassy during the presidential election voting. Media in Moldova, bordering Ukraine, reported the embassy was attacked with Molotov cocktails. No injuries were reported. "A man threw two containers of flammable substances over the fence of the Russian Embassy in Chisinau," police said in a statement.
title: Man arrested in firebomb incident at Russian embassy

description: The Indian Air Force (IAF) has deployed the AF Mi-17 V5 helicopter for several Bambi Bucket operations to extinguish forest fires in the Nilgiris region. Working alongside the forest department and state administration, these helicopters have effectively dispensed more than 16,000 liters of water to contain the fire's advancement.
title: IAF's 'Bambi Bucket' op helps to contain forest fire at Nilgiris

description: Elvish Yadav arrested by Noida Police for snake venom use at a party, leading to a 14-day judicial custody under the Wildlife Protection Act. Accused of supplying snake venom at rave parties.
title: Snake venom case: YouTuber Elvish Yadav sent to 14-days custody

description: Emphasizing the sovereignty and independence of the Maldives, President Mohamed Muizzu stressed that surveillance activities within the country's borders should not be of concern to external entities. While refraining from directly naming any particular nation, his comments come in the wake of the withdrawal of Indian military personnel who had been operating a gifted helicopter from India.
title: Maritime territory no concern of external parties: Maldives prez

description: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu criticized global allies for forgetting the October 7 Hamas attacks and vowed to continue Gaza offensive taking it to Rafah.. He reaffirmed commitment to Rafah operations and said that the military operation would continue along with hostages rescue, and reducing civilian casualties in the ongoing conflict.
title: Netanyahu defies int'l pressure, gives nod to Rafah assault
Foreign students attacked over namaz: 2 held after FIR lodged; MEA contacts Gujarat govt
'PM Modi asks ministers to draft roadmap for first 100 days, next 5 years for new govt'

description: Batting maestro Virat Kohli on Sunday returned to India, following the birth of his son Akaay, and is set to join his franchise Royal Challengers Bangalore's training camp ahead of the upcoming IPL. Kohli had opted out of the India-England Test series citing "personal reasons". Later on, it was announced that the break was taken so that the batting star could be present for the birth of his son in the UK.
title: 'Kohli one of my favourite guys to...': Faf du Plessis

description: According to Ahmedabad city Police Commissioner GS Malik, a group of approximately 200 men reportedly assaulted students from various foreign countries at the Gujarat University hostel in Ahmedabad. The students were allegedly attacked for offering namaz in the hostel premises during the holy month of Ramzan. An FIR was filed against 20-25 individuals, and nine security teams were assembled to investigate the incident.
title: Attack on foreign students: FIR filed, 9 teams formed to catch culprits

description: The Chhattisgarh Economic Offences Wing (EOW) has filed an FIR implicating former Chief Minister Bhupesh Baghel in the Mahadeo Book online betting scam, alleging involvement in a scheme worth around Rs 6,000 crore. Baghel's name appeared in the FIR filed by the EOW based on a complaint from the Enforcement Directorate (ED).
title: Mahadev app case: Ex-CM Bhupesh Baghel named in FIR

description: Hardik Pandya sustained the ankle injury during India's fourth World Cup match against Bangladesh while delivering his first over. Hindered by the injury, he had to leave the field with the assistance of the team's physiotherapist and was unable to participate further in the competition. Pandya expressed that the inability to fully participate in the World Cup would forever burden his heart.
title: 'I got injections, blood removed...': Hardik recalls painful recuperation

description: On Sunday, the Election Commission of India moved the counting date for assembly elections in Arunachal Pradesh and Sikkim from June 4 to June 2. The states' schedules for Parliamentary constituencies have not changed. In an official statement, EC said, "ECI is to conduct election to Legislative Assemblies of Arunachal Pradesh and Sikkim before the cessation of their terms..."
title: EC changes counting date of Arunachal, Sikkim to June 2
Overnight shooting in Washington kills 2, wounds 5

description: Elvish Yadav, the winner of Bigg Boss OTT, has been arrested by the Noida Police in connection with a snake venom case. For further details and updates on this development.
title: Elvish Yadav arrested by Noida Police in snake venom case

description: The opening IPL 2024 clash pits a fight between an idol and disciple as MS Dhoni's CSK takes on Virat Kohli's RCB. This has induced a new layer of excitement in the fans worldwide. Cricbuzz not only guarantees seamless live streaming but also ensures an immersive experience packed with top-notch cricket action and excitement. This season once again promises intense T20 action, with each team playing twice in the round-robin league, brace for thrilling encounters leading to playoffs and a breathtaking finale.
title: When, where & how to watch IPL 2024 online live in US, Canada
Election Commission uploads fresh details on electoral bonds

description: In a significant development, Chevella MP Ranjith Reddy and Khairatabad MLA D Nagender have resigned from BRS party and joined Congress. This move follows BRS MPs switching to BJP, signaling key political shifts in Telangana ahead of Lok Sabha polls.
title: Blow to BRS: Sitting Chevella MP Rajnit Reddy joins Cong

description: Jaishankar defends CAA, citing historical context and international precedents for fast-tracking citizenship based on ethnicity, faith, and social attributes. He questions critics' understanding of history and emphasizes the obligation to minorities affected by Partition.
title: EAM Jaishankar takes on US, other CAA critics

description: Australia secured their sixth title in the 2023 ODI World Cup with a six-wicket win over India at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad last year, as Travis Head's century played a crucial role. Former India batsman Mohammad Kaif criticized India's pitch-preparation strategy, highlighting Cummins' smart decision-making in the final.
title: Kaif's 'doctoring' comment puts Rohit, Dravid under scanner

description: The anticipation to catch glimpse of Virat Kohli, following birth of his son Akaay, finally concluded on Saturday when India's batting maestro was sighted at airport, marking his inaugural appearance ahead of Indian Premier League (IPL) 2024 season. Virat, who was notably absent during the five-match Test series against England, opted to take a hiatus from cricket to support his wife.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli's first appearance since son Akaay's birth

description: Speculation over Virat Kohli's exclusion from India's T20 World Cup squad has been refuted by former India all-rounder Kirti Azad, who claims captain Rohit has told the BCCI that he wants Virat in the squad by all means.  The T20 World Cup, to be jointly hosted by West Indies and the USA, is scheduled to begin on June 2.
title: 'Rohit said we need Virat at any cost for T20 WC'

description: Foreign students injured in Gujarat University attack over namaz. AIMIM chief criticizes Modi. Videos of vandalism viral. SVP Hospital treating. Police investigating. Accused sought. Dr. S Jaishankar role questioned.
title: 5 foreign students injured after brawl over namaz in Gujarat

description: Ather Energy introduces Rizta, an electric scooter tailored for families based on the 450 platform. It aims to meet the growing demand for family-oriented scooters by providing ample space, safety features, and modern technologies.
title: Ather Rizta to get largest storage space in scooter industry: CBO

description: Amid competition and tech layoffs, IBM cuts jobs in marketing and communications. The move aligns with CEO Krishna's focus on AI. Despite layoffs, IBM reports revenue growth, surpassing expectations amidst strong competition in AI development.
title: 7-minute meeting where IBM employees at two divisions were laid off

description: Apple expanding iPad lineup with OLED technology. iPad Air to receive OLED in 2028. Omdia suggests possible OLED foldable device. Improved display quality and power efficiency expected in Apple's future tablets.
title: This is when Apple may launch its first foldable iPhone

description: Prior to the Indian Premier League (IPL) 2024, ex-India cricketer Aakash Chopra noted the commendable consistency displayed by Faf du Plessis and Virat Kohli during the preceding season with the Royal Challengers Bangalore (RCB). Addressing viewers on his official YouTube channel, Chopra highlighted the presence of English batting all-rounder Will Jacks as a backup option for the Bengaluru-based franchise.
title: 'Virat and Faf were...': Ex-cricketer on RCB's batting ahead of IPL 2024

description: In a video posted by the Royals on social media, Jurel is seen entering the hotel while a line of staff stands on either side of a red carpet, saluting the wicketkeeper-batsman as he passes through. The Royals open their IPL 2024 campaign against the Lucknow Super Giants in Jaipur on March 24.
title: Watch: Dhruv Jurel gets 'salute' welcome at Rajasthan Royals

description: London car rally showed support for PM Modi and BJP. Bob Blackman discussed Free Trade Agreement negotiations and Indian economy growth. The event highlighted the strong friendship between India and the UK.
title: Car rally in UK to showcase support for PM Modi ahead of polls

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will attend a huge National Democratic Alliance rally 'Prajagalam,' (the voice of the public), in Palnadu district on Sunday evening, the first joint public assembly of NDA partners in Andhra Pradesh in ten years. PM Modi will be joined in the public meeting by TDP supremo N Chandrababu Naidu.
title: PM Modi to address 1st rally in Andhra with Chandrababu Naidu

description: Under the gentle caress of a spring breeze at M A Chidambaram Stadium, an unforgettable evening unfolded for R Ashwin and the assembled crowd. Celebrating Ashwin's remarkable milestone of 100 Test matches and 500 wickets in the longest format, the Chennai cricket community came together to honor their beloved No. 1 star. It was a poignant journey down memory lane for the champion spinner, reflecting on how the seeds of his illustrious career were planted nearly 16 years ago.
title: A chance contract and how it turned around for R Ashwin

description: Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal summoned by the Enforcement Directorate on March 21 in a money laundering case linked to excise policy. This marks the ninth summons under PMLA. Kejriwal, leader of AAP, has refused to comply with past summons, citing them as illegal. Recent bail granted in two complaints. BRS leader K Kavitha apprehended.
title: Excise policy case: ED issues fresh summons to Kejriwal

description: Narendra Modi laid the foundation for semiconductor plants in India. Ministry banned OTT platforms hosting obscene content. Paytm got NPCI licence; CCI probing Google. US House passed TikTok ban bill; Airbnb addressed privacy concerns.
title: PM Modi lays foundation of chip plants, 'porn ban' on OTT channels & more

description: Joy returns to the home of late Punjabi singer Sidhu Moosewala as his mother, Charan Kaur, gives birth to a baby boy. Moosewala's father, Balkaur Singh, shares the delightful news on social media, bringing happiness to fans. Despite Moosewala's tragic demise on May 29, 2022, his music lives on with posthumous releases.
title: Sidhu Moosewala's mother Charan Kaur gives birth to baby boy

description: Suspensions and transfers in Bareilly Central Jail after murder accused's viral live stream. Asif Khan hints at release while authorities investigate. Khan accused of murdering Rakesh Yadav in Shahjahanpur.
title: 'I am in heaven': Murder accused streams live video from jail

description: Starbucks closes Web3 program Odyssey, shifting focus from NFTs to AI. Potential program return mentioned. Adam Brotman leads transition to Nifty NFT. Steve Kaczynski shares insights on active participants and 'The Everything Token'.
title: Starbucks is ending its 'futuristic' loyalty program

description: Amnesty International, in collaboration with a coalition of human rights activists and civil society organizations, has urgently called upon the Pakistani government to promptly restore social media platform “X,” which has been blocked in the country for a month now.
title: Amnesty to Pakistan: Restore Elon Musk's social media platform
UP man kills student with screwdriver, drives with body for 7hrs

description: Keen, Google's Pinterest competitor launched in 2020, ceases on March 24th, 2024. Users can preserve data. Its experimental closure shapes future recommendation systems. We know many of you have invested time on Keen. To make sure this effort is not lost, we have created a tool to let you download your Keen data to a local zip file -- i.e. links you curated, images you uploaded, and text posts you own.
title: Google is shutting down this photo sharing app

description: Donald Trump declared on Saturday that the November presidential elections would be the "most important date" in US history, warning of a "bloodbath for the whole" if he does not win. "Now if I don't get elected it's going to be a bloodbath for the whole, that's going to be the least of it, it's going to be a bloodbath for the country", he said.
title: 'Bloodbath': Trump warns if he loses US prez elections

description: It seemed like a redux of last year's showdown, with Delhi Capitals poised to clash once more with Mumbai Indians in the final. However, under the leadership of Smriti Mandhana, Royal Challengers Bangalore orchestrated a stunning upset, turning the tables on MI in the Eliminator on Friday. Now, Mandhana's RCB will square off against Meg Lanning's DC at the bustling Arun Jaitley Stadium this Sunday.
title: WPL Final: Maiden title beckons Delhi Capitals, RCB
Lok Sabha polls: 10 major factors that hold the key to this battle

description: Xiaomi to introduce Xiaomi Pulse water gun in India around Holi. Features 2 firing modes, automatic refill, energy accumulation, dynamic lighting effects, 25 water bombs, 7-9 meters range, and high-definition tactical display for launch mode.
title: After phones, Xiaomi could be launching a water gun in India this holi

description: Man fined for false mental claims against wife by high court. She proved her sanity with documents. The attempt to annul marriage based on her intelligence level was rejected by the court.
title: HC slaps Rs 50k cost after man seeks wife's mental health test
Visitors to UK can now work remotely
IPL won't be shifted out of India: BCCI

description: Union minister Nitin Gadkari dismissed rumours of discord with deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis, asserting he played a pivotal role in Fadnavis’ political journey. Emphasizing his grassroots approach, Gadkari highlighted his preference for a non-political career and commitment to serving as an RSS volunteer. In an interview with TOI, he clarified his stance on various issues.
title: Not in PM race, I am neta by conviction, not by calculation: Gadkari
